records.name: Aaron
records.introduction:
The annual Consumer Electronics Show (CES) kicked off on January 7, 2020. According to the statistics of interchain Pulse, there are 34 blockchain companies participating in the exhibition, which is concentrated in Sands and Hall. There are also several blockchain forums.

In terms of quantity, there are not many blockchain enterprises participating in the exhibition, but their fields are widely distributed and of high quality, and there are industrial forms that are not available in domestic blockchain. CES has also become a window into the development of blockchain around the world.

Bright spot for overseas blockchain companies
